1 (b) (1) (i) The county governing body shall provide sufficient funding to
2 meet the minimum compensation levels required under this section.
3 (ii) Within the limits authorized by the county governing body, a
4 local board may fix the compensation of election judges above the minimum compensation
5 levels required under this section.
6 (2) A local board shall pay an election judge for:
7 (i) SUBJECT TO PARAGRAPH (4)(II) OF THIS SUBSECTION, each
8 course of instruction required under § 10–206(g)(1) of this subtitle that the election judge
9 completes; and
10 (ii) each election day and each early voting day that the election
11 judge actually serves.
12 (3) (i) For each election judge who is not a returning election judge, the
13 compensation for each election day and each early voting day actually served shall be at
14 least $250 per day.
15 (ii) For each returning election judge, the compensation for each
16 election day and each early voting day actually served shall be at least $100 more per day
17 than the compensation provided to an election judge who is not a returning election judge.
18 (4) (I) The compensation for each completed course of instruction
19 required under § 10–206(g)(1) of this subtitle shall be at least $50.
20 (II) A LOCAL BOARD SHALL PAY AN ELECTION JUDGE THE
21 COMPENSATION REQUIRED UNDER PARAGRAPH (2)(I) OF THIS SUBSECTION ONLY
22 AFTER THE ELECTION JUDGE ACTUALLY SERVES AN ELECTION DAY OR EARLY
23 VOTING DAY.
24 (c) The State Board shall reimburse each local board for $50 of the additional
25 compensation required under subsection (b)(3)(ii) of this section that is paid to each
26 returning election judge.
27 (D) FOR SERVICE AS AN ELECTION JUDGE, A PUBLIC SCHOOL STUDENT IN
28 THE STATE MAY BOTH:
29 (1) EARN HOURS TOWARD THE SERVICE–LEARNING REQUIREMENT
30 FOR GRADUATION UNDER COMAR 13A.03.02.05; AND
31 (2) RECEIVE THE ELECTION JUDGE COMPENSATION UNDER THIS
32 SECTION.

